# Define this one. It will add a function to monitor mbufs,
# whether you change the MBUF pool size or not.
ARCH_DEP_CFLAGS += -DEPICS_RTEMS

# To change the pool size, uncomment the following and adjust
# as needed. The values are in kB. The default values are:
#
#   180kB for mbufs     (1440 mbufs, 128 bytes each)
#   350kB for clusters  (175 clusters, 2048 bytes each)
#
# The final numbers should be balanced. With the default values,
# there are ~8.4x more mbufs than clusters. With the example below
# (taken from MVME6100), there are 6.2x more mbufs than clusters.
#
# Most network operations fit on 1, maybe 2 regular mbufs.
# Clusters are used only with larger (> 208 bytes) payloads. So,
# having smaller mbuf/cluster ratio would make sense only on the
# base of actual traffic, if we know it's needed.
#
ARCH_DEP_CFLAGS += -DRTEMS_NETWORK_CONFIG_MBUF_SPACE=2048
ARCH_DEP_CFLAGS += -DRTEMS_NETWORK_CONFIG_CLUSTER_SPACE=5120
